  "description": "Single-page overview of scheduled backups for the homelab, covering both the Restic repository layer and the application-level Nextcloud backup.\n\nWorkflow: start from freshness and last-run status to confirm backups are recent and succeeding, then correlate run duration across layers to spot shared bottlenecks or layer-specific slowdowns. Finally, review data volume and growth by comparing Restic added data from the last successful run with the size of the last successful Nextcloud backup.\n\nRow 1: hours since last success, last exit status, and a scrape sanity check for backup metrics.\nRow 2: run duration per layer, overlaid to highlight correlation and contention.\nRow 3: data volume and growth signals for Restic and Nextcloud backups.\n\nData source: Prometheus, fed by node_exporter textfile collector metrics. Thresholds are aligned with the corresponding Prometheus backup alerts.\n\nSecurity: Backup metrics can reveal storage capacity, retention cadence, and operational schedules. Restrict access and avoid sharing raw exports without redaction.",
